benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/phase - Retrieve phase for a given subscription and date

covered: Valid Request: TC01 verifies 200 with application/json and a Phase object; TC15 covers correctness on a phase-boundary date.
Query Parameters: TC01–TC08 and TC14 exercise combinations (both provided, one missing, none, invalid formats, extra/unsupported params) with appropriate 200/400/404 outcomes.
Empty Response/No Data: TC05 (non-existent subscription), TC08 (date outside active period), and TC12 (empty DB) assert 404 behavior.
Authorization: TC09 covers 401 for missing/invalid auth token.
Input Validation & Security: TC06 (invalid UUID), TC07 (invalid date), and TC11 (SQL injection attempt) validate robust input handling and no internal error leakage.
Error Handling: TC10 covers dependency failure with 503 Service Unavailable.
Performance/Scalability: TC13 (large dataset) and TC16 (concurrent requests) validate latency and concurrency expectations.
Produces/Content-Type: TC01 checks Content-Type application/json as per Produces requirement.
gaps: Caching Behavior: No scenarios validate ETag/Cache-Control/Last-Modified headers or conditional GET (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since) and 304 Not Modified.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling behavior (e.g., 429 Too Many Requests) or X-RateLimit-* and Retry-After headers under burst traffic.
Authorization Depth: No 403 Forbidden scenario for authenticated users lacking permissions/tenant scope.
Ambiguous Missing-Parameter Semantics: TC02 allows multiple outcomes (“200 or default”), and behaviors for omitted params are not asserted deterministically per spec.
Response Schema Validation: Tests say “valid Phase object” but don’t validate the response against a Phase JSON schema; error response structure is not validated either.
Content Negotiation: No tests for Accept headers (e.g., ensuring 200 for Accept: application/json and 406 or defined fallback for unsupported media types).
Date Edge Cases: No checks for calendar edge cases like leap days (e.g., 2024-02-29), invalid dates (e.g., 2023-02-29), or extreme future/past dates.
recommendations: Add caching tests: verify Cache-Control and ETag/Last-Modified on 200 responses; send If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since to assert 304 Not Modified when appropriate.

Add rate limiting tests: issue bursts exceeding limits to assert 429 and validate X-RateLimit-Remaining/Reset and Retry-After headers; ensure TC16 does not inadvertently trigger throttling in normal concurrency.
Expand authorization coverage: include a 403 Forbidden test for a valid token without required permissions or wrong tenant, alongside the existing 401.
Make missing-parameter behavior deterministic: align with API contract (default phase vs error) and split TC02/TC03/TC04 into precise expectations with single outcomes.
Introduce JSON schema validation: enforce the Phase object shape (required fields/types) and a consistent error schema (code/message/type) across all negative cases.
Test content negotiation: assert 200 for Accept: application/json and 406 (or defined fallback) for unsupported Accept values; continue verifying Content-Type.
Add calendar edge-case scenarios: leap day valid/invalid, month-end boundaries, and far-future/past requestedDate values to ensure stable date handling.
Enhance 5xx handling checks: for TC10, also assert presence/format of Retry-After and that sensitive internals are not leaked in error responses.
